e":"text","text":"It takes a render buffer ID ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"sourceType"},{"type":"text","text":" == GL_RENDERBUFFER) or a texture"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"id ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"sourceType"},{"type":"text","text":" == GL_TEXTURE) and draws it onto "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"cr"},{"type":"text","text":" with an OVER operation,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"respecting the current clip. The top left corner of the rectangle specified"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"by "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"x"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"y"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"width"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"height"},{"type":"text","text":" will be drawn at the current (0,0) position of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"cairo_t"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This will work for "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"all"}]},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"cairo_t"},{"type":"text","text":", as long as "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"surface"},{"type":"text","text":" is realized, but the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"fallback implementation that reads back the pixels from the buffer may be"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"used in the general case. In the case of direct drawing to a surface with"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"no special effects applied to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"cr"},{"type":"text","text":" it will however use a more efficient"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"approach."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For GL_RENDERBUFFER the code will always fall back to software for buffers"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"with alpha components, so make sure you use GL_TEXTURE if using alpha."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Calling this may change the current GL context."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"cairo_draw_from_gl is deprecated:"}]},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The function is overly complex and produces broken output"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"in various combinations of arguments. If you want to draw with GL textures"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"in GTK, use [ctor@Gdk.GLTexture.new]; if you want to use that texture in"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Cairo, use [method@Gdk.Texture.download] to download the data into a Cairo"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"image surface."}]}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"sections":[],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/gdk\/surfaceref\/cairodrawfromgl(cr:source:sourcetype:bufferscale:x:y:width:height:)"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/Gdk\/documentation\/Gdk\/SurfaceRef\/cairoDrawFromGl(cr:source:sourceType:bufferScale:x:y:width:height:)","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The main way to not draw GL content in GTK."}],"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"Gdk"}],"role":"symbol","title":"cairoDrawFromGl(cr:source:sourceType:bufferScale:x:y:width:height:)","roleHeading":"Instance Method","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"cairoDrawFromGl"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"kind":"genericParameter","text":"cairoContextT"},{"kind":"text","text":">("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"cr"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"cairoContextT"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"source"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":